    "body": "It  would be helpful to have some documentation on how to use the flattener, especially with contracts with a lot of imports, libraries etc.  I gather if I use 'npx hardhat flatten > Output.sol' its going to put my entire project in a single library. which is not what I need.  I am deploying contracts on a non-hardhat backend service and need to verify for them on etherscan as they are created, so I just need the flattened version of the contract and its dependencies, but its just not clear how to work the flattener.  Seems like if you provide a tool, even minimal documentation would be better than nothing.",
