    "body": "@grapevinegizmos this is the output of `npx hardhat help flatten` or `npx hardhat flatten --help`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nHardhat version 2.12.3\r\n\r\nUsage: hardhat [GLOBAL OPTIONS] flatten [...files]\r\n\r\nPOSITIONAL ARGUMENTS:\r\n\r\n  files\tThe files to flatten \r\n\r\nflatten: Flattens and prints contracts and their dependencies\r\n\r\nFor global options help run: hardhat help\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat I get from your comment is that it's not clear what happens if you don't pass any files? If that's the case, would this be better in your opinion?\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nUsage: hardhat [GLOBAL OPTIONS] flatten [...files]\r\n\r\nPOSITIONAL ARGUMENTS:\r\n\r\n  files\tThe files to flatten. If no file is passed, all the contracts in the project will be flattened.\r\n\r\nflatten: Flattens and prints contracts and their dependencies\r\n```",
