    "body": "Thank you @grapevinegizmos, that's very useful feedback.\r\n\r\nI opened https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/pull/3429 with a new guide about flattening contracts. You can check the preview [here](https://hardhat-git-add-flatten-guide-nomic-foundation.vercel.app/hardhat-runner/docs/advanced/flattening).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> Thanks. Now I am fighting with verify, same sort of issues around constructor arguments. I took me a lot of fooling around to figure out how to put more than one constructor argument on the command line, whether they need quotes, commas etc. and that apparently there is no way to verify on the command line if the constructor takes a struct as an argument etc.\r\n> \r\n> All of this would be a lot easier with just a few more examples of the right way to do it in the documentation on the website\r\n\r\nThere are some examples in [the guide](https://hardhat-git-add-flatten-guide-nomic-foundation.vercel.app/hardhat-runner/docs/guides/verifying) and more info in the [plugin's page](https://hardhat-git-add-flatten-guide-nomic-foundation.vercel.app/hardhat-runner/plugins/nomiclabs-hardhat-etherscan). That looks complete to me, but if you think it can be improved, feel free to send a PR or to open an issue with suggestions.",
